cellExpression.summary: Mainly localized to the Golgi apparatus. In addition localized to the nucleoplasm.

image.description: Immunofluorescent staining of human cell line U-251 MG shows localization to the Golgi apparatus.

assayDescription.description: Co-localization with the cis-Golgi marker GM130/GOLGA2 (RRID:AB_398141) for a refined protein localization within the Golgi apparatus in U-2 OS cells. RHBDD2 localizes to the entire Golgi apparatus.

verification.description: Pass with quality comment low specificity (binding to 1-2 PrESTs >15% and <40%).

tissueExpression.summary: Neuronal cells and hematopoietic tissue displayed strong granular cytoplasmic staining. Moderate positivity was observed in glial cells of cerebral cortex, seminal vesicle, Leydig cells and thyroid. Remaining normal tissues were negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Mainly not consistent with RNA expression data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human cerebral cortex shows strong cytoplasmic positivity in neuronal cells.

tissueExpression.summary: A rare case of glioma displayed moderate cytoplasmic staining. Moderate nuclear positivity was observed in a single case of melanoma. Most remaining cancer tissues were negative.
